{"type":"after","callId":"call@173","endTime":5238.164,"result":{"value":{"s":"🎲\nBoardgame.sh\nGames\nVI\n🐺 Werewolf Online\n\nFree multiplayer social deduction game. Secret roles, hidden wolves, and one village to save.\n\n● Connected\nLeave\n🐺\nPlayer1\n•\nWolf\nYour Role\n\nRead your role carefully — don't let others see!\n\n🐺\nWolf\n\nYou are a Wolf! Work with your pack to eliminate Villagers each night. Pretend to be innocent during the day.\n\nGoal: Wolves ≥ Villagers\nProceed to Night 🌙\nHow to Play Werewolf\n1\nCreate or join a room\n\nThe host creates a room and shares the 6-character code. Other players enter the code to join on their own devices.\n\n2\nReceive your secret role\n\nEach player privately views their role — Wolf or Villager. Don't show anyone your screen!\n\n3\nNight Phase\n\nWolves secretly vote to eliminate a Villager. Villagers wait with eyes closed.\n\n4\nDay Phase\n\nEveryone discusses who might be a Wolf. After the timer ends, players vote to eliminate one suspect.\n\n5\nWin the game\n\nVillagers win by eliminating all Wolves. Wolves win when they equal or outnumber the Villagers.\n\nRoles Guide\n🐺\nWolf\n\nWolves know who their teammates are. Each night, wolves vote together to eliminate a villager. During the day, they must blend in and avoid suspicion.\n\n🏡\nVillager\n\nVillagers have no special abilities but outnumber the wolves at the start. Use logic, observation, and persuasion to identify and vote out the wolves.\n\nStrategy Tips\n💡 Watch for inconsistencies\n\nWolves often contradict themselves. Keep track of what everyone says across rounds.\n\n💡 Silence is suspicious\n\nPlayers who say little and avoid taking a stance are often trying to stay under the radar.\n\n💡 Wolves should act natural\n\nThe best wolf players express genuine concern about finding wolves — without overdoing it.\n\n💡 Use the vote strategically\n\nIf you're a villager, never vote with zero reasoning. Share your logic to build trust and rally others.\n\nFrequently Asked Questions\nHow many players does Werewolf need?\n\nThe game works with as few as 3 players, but the ideal experience is 6–12. More players means more chaos, more deduction, and more fun.\n\nDo players need separate devices?\n\nYes — each player needs their own phone or computer so they can receive their secret role privately. The game runs on any modern browser.\n\nHow does the room code work?\n\nThe host creates a room and gets a unique 6-character code. Share it via chat, voice call, or just read it aloud. Players enter it on the join screen.\n\nWhat happens if someone disconnects?\n\nThe game state is saved on the server. If a player refreshes the page or reconnects with the same player ID, they rejoin their room automatically.\n\nCan the host change the number of wolves?\n\nYes. The host can adjust the wolf count and discussion timer length in the Settings panel before starting the game.\n\nIs Werewolf free to play?\n\nCompletely free — no account, no downloads, no paywalls. Just create a room and share the code.\n\nLooking for a different game?\n\n🃏 Try Truth or Dare →\n\nPrivacy Policy  ·  © 2025 Boardgame.sh"}},"afterSnapshot":"after@call@173"}
